ðŸ§© 2D Array â€” Declaration + Initialization Rules :
--------------------------------------------------
ðŸ‘‰ Way 1: Declare and Then Initialize
int[][] arr;                 // Declaration
        arr = new int[3][4];   // Initialization with size 3x4

ðŸ‘‰ Way 2: Declare + Initialize Together 
int [][] arr = new int [3][2];
Note:- 
      - First one like,  [3] â†’ tells Number of rows , Yaani array me 3 rows hongi.
      - second one like, [2] â†’ tells Number of columns in each row , Har row ke andar 2 elements honge.

ðŸ‘‰ Way 3: Directly Assign Values (Shortcut using {})
int [][] arr = { â†“0  â†“1 <- column
      rows -> 0  {1,2},   
      rows -> 1  {4,5},
      rows -> 2  {8,9}
                       };
Note:- This is actually shortcut for:  int[][] arr = new int[][] {
                                                                    {10, 20},
                                                                    {30, 40},
                                                                    {50, 60}
                                                                             };
                                                                     Compiler automatically adds: new int[][]


ðŸ§© Ways to Traverse a 2D Array :
---------------------------------

ðŸ“Œ 1. Normal For Loop (Nested Loops) :
for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {            // row
    for (int j = 0; j < arr[i].length; j++) {     // column
        System.out.println(arr[i][j]);
    }
}

ðŸ“Œ 2. For-Each Loop :
for (int[] row : arr) {
    for (int value : row) {
        System.out.println(value);
    }
}

ðŸ“Œ 3. While Loop :
int i = 0;
while (i < arr.length) {
    int j = 0;
    while (j < arr[i].length) {
        System.out.println(arr[i][j]);
        j++;
    }
    i++;
}

ðŸ“Œ 5. Stream API (Java 8+) :
A. Printing each row :
                  Arrays.stream(arr).forEach(row -> System.out.println(Arrays.toString(row)));
B. Printing each element :
                          Arrays.stream(arr)
                                .flatMapToInt(Arrays::stream)
                                .forEach(System.out::println);






Q1. Follow up Question :                                                              
Write a Java program to create a 2D integer array with 3 rows and 2 columns.
Take integer input from the user to fill the array and then print all the elements.
Expected Input :
1 2 3 4 5 6
also write code for printing it . 
output :
1 2
3 4
5 6
Note:- in 2D array if you want to deal with all elements (rows and columns) then 2 loops are required.



